beer.beer_description:
It is in this remote Siberian peninsula that Frenchies is born. 
Thomas and Vince were crossing the wilderness of Kamchatka in autonomy during 2 month. Fighting hunger with dreams of endless feasts of food and beers, the Frenchies concept was born.  Following the foot steps of captain Lapérouse Thomas and Vince then moved to Australia to fulfil this dream.
 Today we are releasing the original beer. Black like the volcanic soil of Kamchatka. With it’s mighty 6.1% you will taste the power of this earth, yet it will feel like a walk in a park.
Malty with chocolate, vanilla and subtle fruit on the nose, this black bière de garde is surprisingly lean and refreshing. The rich malty sweet flavours are balanced by a dry and extra smooth finish.
